The paper proposes an algorithm for signal recovery from compressed measurements, which is a common problem in information theory (cs.IT). The algorithm is based on a greedy search strategy, which is a common approach in machine learning (cs.LG) and signal processing (cs.SP). The paper also discusses the performance guarantee of the algorithm using the restricted isometry property (RIP), which is a common technique in numerical analysis (cs.NA) and signal processing (cs.SI).
